mvc.models

Class ClassContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • mvc.models.ClassContainer

  • class ClassContainer
extends java.lang.Object
    This class calculates and hold all the information necessary for every class in a model.
    Author:
    Hubert Lemelin

      • name

      • superclasses

        List of direct superclasses.

      • subclasses

        protected java.util.ArrayList<ClassContainer> subclasses
        List of direct subclasses.

      • attributes

        protected java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> attributes
        List of attributes. We use a HashMap to easily check if an attribute already exists.

      • operations

        protected java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.ArrayList<OperationContainer>> operations
        List of methods. At the outer level, in the HashMap, we use the name of the operation as the key. The the inner level, in an ArrayList we store all the OperationContainer instances of the operations with the same name as the key (the name of the operation). It is easier this way to check if a duplicate of an operation exists.

      • associations

        protected java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,InnerAssociationContainer> associations
        List of association. We use an HashMap to detect duplicate association names.

      • aggregations

        protected java.util.ArrayList<InnerAggregationContainer> aggregations
        List of aggregations.

      • attributeNamesCache

        protected java.lang.String[] attributeNamesCache
        Cache of the names of the attributes.

      • allSuperclassesCache

        protected ClassContainer[] allSuperclassesCache
        Cache of all the ClassContainer instances of all direct/indirect superclasses. Using a cache reduce the number of computation required.

      • allSubclassesCache

        protected ClassContainer[] allSubclassesCache
        Cache of all the ClassContainer instances of all direct/indirect subclasses. Using a cache reduce the number of computation required.

      • attributesCache

        protected java.lang.String[] attributesCache
        Cache of the type/name of the attributes. Used by the model to send data to the view. This way, we can unlink the attribute objects and only keep a String array. It frees some memory.

      • operationsCache

        protected java.lang.String[] operationsCache
        Cache of the type/name/signature of the methods. Used by the model to send data to the view. This way, we can unlink the operation objects and only keep a String array. It frees some memory.

      • subclassesCache

        protected java.lang.String[] subclassesCache
        Cache of the names of the superclasses. Used by the model to send data to the view. This way, delete the structure holding the references to other ClassContainer (which won't be deleted) and only keep a String array. It frees some memory.

      • superclassesCache

        protected java.lang.String[] superclassesCache
        Cache of the names of the subclasses. Used by the model to send data to the view. This way, delete the structure holding the references to other ClassContainer (which won't be deleted) and only keep a String array. It frees some memory.

      • associationsCache

        protected AssociationContainer[] associationsCache
        Cache of the associations by using a very simple container class. Used by the model to send data to the view. This way, we can delete the structure holding the data of associations. It frees some memory.

      • aggregationsCache

        protected AggregationContainer[] aggregationsCache
        Cache of the aggregations by using a very simple container class. Used by the model to send data to the view. This way, we can delete the structure holding the data of associations. It frees some memory.

      • metricsCache

        protected java.lang.String[] metricsCache
        Cache of the calculated metrics. Used by the model to send data to the view.

      • metrics

        protected java.lang.String[][] metrics
        An array of arrays of String. Each outer level is one metric. In the inner level are only two elements: the name of the metric and the value of the metric.

      • addAggregation

        void addAggregation(Aggregation aggregation,
                    boolean isContainer,
                    java.lang.String details)
        Adds an aggregation to the class.
        Parameters:
        aggregation - The instance of Aggregation containing the data about the aggregation to be added.
        isContainer - true if the current class is the "container class", false if the current class if a "part class" of the aggregation.
        details - If the current class is the container, it contains a String of all its "part classes". Otherwise, if the current class is a "part", it contains the name of the "container class".

      • createException

        protected ModelException createException(ModelException.ERRORS error)
